left for the Trump
administration?

27:40.692 --> 27:42.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM, Former U.S. Deputy
Assistant
Secretary of Defense: Well, no,
I think that

27:42.594 --> 27:47.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that's an accurate recounting of
the way that
things were presented to the
Trump administration

27:47.332 --> 27:51.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and to the Obama administration
before the
-- before the Trump
inauguration.

27:51.737 --> 27:55.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that we in the Obama
administration,
those are of us who served in
the Obama administration

27:55.707 --> 28:00.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
need to be very careful as we
criticize the
process that the Trump
administration used

28:00.212 --> 28:01.947 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to approve this.

28:01.980 --> 28:05.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First off, to approve this raid,
it would
have gone through several
hurdles just through

28:05.450 --> 28:09.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Department of Defense before
being presented
to the president.

28:09.421 --> 28:13.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
When we in the Obama
administration brought
these options to the president,
it followed

28:13.492 --> 28:16.161 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a very deliberate interagency
process.

28:16.194 --> 28:18.864 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's what worked for President
Obama.

28:18.897 --> 28:24.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Just because we have seen, quite
frankly,
a lot of a -- lot of mess in the
Trump administration

28:24.903 --> 28:28.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
thus far in their first month, I
