to once again
send humans to the moon.

33:07.686 --> 33:10.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But first: the nation's opioid
crisis.

33:10.655 --> 33:16.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Overdose deaths are on the rise
across the
country, in 2015, surpassing gun
homicides

33:16.228 --> 33:17.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the first time.

33:17.896 --> 33:21.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the hardest-hit states is
Maryland,
where the governor today
declared a state

33:22.000 --> 33:24.169 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of emergency to fight the
epidemic.

33:24.202 --> 33:29.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, for more than a year, the
city of Baltimore
has been training everyday
citizens in how

33:29.875 --> 33:35.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to use a lifesaving antidote, an
approach
that's catching on across the
country.

33:35.113 --> 33:39.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"NewsHour" producer Pamela
Kirkland visited
Baltimore to find out more.

33:39.551 --> 33:42.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Excuse me, sir, are you
interested in
Narcan training?

33:42.120 --> 33:45.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: Each week, city
health workers
hit the streets of Baltimore,
handing out

33:45.790 --> 33:49.160 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
