33:52.330 --> 33:57.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: Naloxone, brand
name Narcan,
comes as a nasal spray or
injection, and works

33:57.068 --> 34:00.272 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by blocking the brain's opioid
receptors.

34:00.305 --> 34:06.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a city with 24,000 active
heroin users,
overdoses, and now increasingly
this emergency

34:06.278 --> 34:08.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
antidote have become facts of
life.

34:08.580 --> 34:12.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: I lost a friend of mine
that was -- at
25 years old.

34:12.851 --> 34:19.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: I have just seen so many
young people
getting hooked on the opioids,
or better yet,

34:19.791 --> 34:20.759 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the fentanyl.

34:20.792 --> 34:22.560 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it's definitely a killer,

34:22.594 --> 34:26.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: In Maryland,
deaths from
opioids, which include heroin,
fentanyl and

34:26.298 --> 34:32.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
prescription painkillers,
doubled between
2010 and 2015, to just under
1,100 people

34:32.704 --> 34:34.139 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
