20-fold.

34:45.550 --> 34:47.352 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:47.385 --> 34:50.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEANA WEN, Baltimore Health
Commissioner:
We have an epidemic of people,
fellow residents

34:50.221 --> 34:53.325 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in our city, who are dying from
opioid overdose.

34:53.358 --> 34:58.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: In late 2015,
Dr. Leana Wen,
Baltimore's health commissioner,
and a practicing

34:58.964 --> 35:05.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
emergency room physician, issued
a standing
order for naloxone to all
620,000 city residents.

35:05.170 --> 35:07.005 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:07.038 --> 35:10.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEANA WEN: What that means is
that, if somebody
goes through a very basic
training -- and

35:10.809 --> 35:16.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we do trainings everywhere,
including on street
corners, in jails, in public
housing, really

35:16.548 --> 35:21.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
anywhere that people are -- they
will immediately
get a prescription for naloxone,
and even

35:21.920 --> 35:23.321 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
get the medication in hand.

35:23.355 --> 35:27.592 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAMELA KIRKLAND: Just one dose
